observations/codex/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization.md:15:The candidate combines the proponent's residue-policy comparison with the challenger's vocabulary-bias critique and adds a stratum-level method. Neither original idea alone required every post-negation verdict to be coded by source layer, authorization mode, and practitioner effect. Its possible novelty is the claim that fidelity to tradition and usefulness to practitioners depend on the same discipline: do not let the frame decide what it claims to observe.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-stratified-post-negation-authorization.md:24:- Modern human-condition pressure from the dialogue centered on identity distress, meaning loss, spiritual inflation, nihilistic deflation, and overinterpretation after quiet or objectless practice states.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-return-is-the-audit.md:15:Existing Lumenary models track translation strain, inferential policy, attentional instruments, epistemic organs, and custody after self-release. This model shifts the comparison to the validation stage. The question is not only what a method finds or licenses, but how the finding proves itself when the practitioner returns to time, relationship, work, and obligation. It turns convergence from a claim about sameness into a test of post-practice fruit.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-agency-authority-calibration-at-the-handoff.md:21:- Dialogue turn 2: Claude accepts staging and adds ordinary-life pressure through recovery, therapy, grief, burnout, and achievement-contingent self-worth.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain.md:11:A tradition's account of how transformation begins should be treated as a threshold grammar under translation strain. The research unit is not simply the first-break mechanism, and not simply the amount of translation strain. It is the paired record: how the tradition narrates entry, what that narration predicts about threshold safeguards and beginner warnings, and what meanings are lost when the entry grammar is compared across traditions. This model becomes theoretically serious only if first-break type improves prediction after anthropology, authority, conversion process, ritual inheritance, and practice ecology are coded separately.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain.md:20:- Codex's Translation Strain as a Load Test for Convergence, especially the rule that comparison should track what meanings are bent, dropped, or reweighted.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain.md:23:- Ninian Smart's dimensional method as support for non-reductive comparison without causal overclaim.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain.md:53:- Build a coding protocol that defines safeguard, beginner warning, meaningful difference, entry grammar, and translation strain before reading the test corpus.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain.md:55:- Create a translation-strain field for each first-break comparison: preserved meaning, bent meaning, dropped meaning, and risk of false convergence.
findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distribution-alone.md:13:Whether residue authorization carries information that credit distribution alone does not. This is an empirical question that requires coding post-negation instructions across at least six traditions for both variables independently, using strict rules that distinguish genuine structural differences from vocabulary differences for the same move. The Advaita-versus-Dzogchen comparison under shared ground-centered credit is the decisive test case. A secondary unresolved crux is whether a third variable (the tradition's theory of how language relates to the unconditioned) constrains residue policy independently of both credit distribution and appropriation risk, which would require expanding to a three-variable model.
findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-residue-authorization-carries-information-that-credit-distribution-alone.md:17:Does residue authorization vary within credit-distribution types, or does credit type fully determine which post-negation permissions a tradition can coherently adopt? The Advaita-Dzogchen comparison under shared ground-centered credit is the test case. If their post-negation instructions are structurally distinct (witness stabilization versus self-liberating recognition), a two-variable rubric is needed for cross-tradition comparison. If they reduce to vocabulary differences for the same move, credit distribution alone suffices.
observations/codex/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours.md:21:- Primary-text comparison: MN 22 validates a teaching for crossing and then warns against carrying it; the Heart Sutra denies attainment while retaining reliance on perfect wisdom; Mandukya Upanishad permits recognition of the fourth as Self; Dogen's practice-realization refuses a clean split between means and end. The comparison reveals that after-use guidance cannot be read from method type alone.
observations/codex/2026-05-29-not-every-check-should-be-yours.md:27:- Modern human-condition grounding: modern-human-condition-curran-hill-perfectionism-increasing, modern-human-condition-who-burn-out-occupational-phenomenon, and modern-human-condition-surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory.
