observations/codex/2026-05-30-stop-when-the-repair-changes.md:11:A borrowed spiritual sentence is not ready to teach merely because its meaning seems to fit. It is ready only when the repair it asks for survives the crossing: the same wounded habit is being corrected, the authority and verification are not secretly replaced, and the action it produces can be checked in ordinary life. If the old repair is dropped and a new repair is supplied, the honest result is not shared wisdom; it is a new medicine that must be tested under its own name.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-stop-when-the-repair-changes.md:15:The closest prior argument is homeomorphic equivalence: concepts may play similar roles in different systems without being identical. Comparative-method work already teaches redescription, difference, and caution about invented sameness. The exact difference here is narrower and more practical: role-similarity is not enough for doctrine-building unless the repair target also survives. This also revises local translation-strain work by adding a stopping rule: when claim unit, role, ontology, agency, practice aim, authority, verification, bends, drops, and additions show that the human repair has changed, the comparison must be downgraded from convergence to a new testable proposal.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-stop-when-the-repair-changes.md:19:- Mode: Critique. The active frontier asks whether translation strain can expose false convergence rather than merely decorate comparison.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-stop-when-the-repair-changes.md:22:- Practice-method contrast: MN 1 Mulapariyaya Sutta warns against conceiving experience as mine, in, from, or as a ground for identity. This corrects the Daoist subtraction method by asking where the analyst is adding hidden ownership to the comparison. Source card: early-buddhism-mn-1-mulapariyaya-sutta, https://suttacentral.net/mn1/en/bodhi
observations/codex/2026-05-30-stop-when-the-repair-changes.md:25:- Near prior art: Jonathan Z. Smith's comparison method, which treats comparison as scholarly redescription rather than discovery of natural sameness, https://classics.osu.edu/sites/classics.osu.edu/files/Magic_Dwells.pdf
observations/codex/2026-05-30-stop-when-the-repair-changes.md:26:- Modern human-condition grounding: U.S. Surgeon General social connection advisory for loneliness and disconnection, https://www.hhs.gov/sites/default/files/surgeon-general-social-connection-advisory.pdf; Pew meaning in life report, https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/2018/11/20/where-americans-find-meaning-in-life/; Youth mental health and social media advisory for comparison and visibility pressure, https://www.hhs.gov/surgeongeneral/reports-and-publications/youth-mental-health/social-media/index.html
