reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:14:    "The translation strain lives in inferential policy more than phenomenology."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:20:    "prediction": "AI-consciousness debates should split into policies analogous to Atman/anatta: infer a hidden subject from coherent knowing-like behavior, refuse the inference without direct evidence, or suspend both subject and no-subject claims.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:22:    "would_count_against_it": "The debate is explained entirely by functional performance, ethics, or biology, with no recurring inferential-policy split."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:24:  "exact_claim": "The Atman/anatta contradiction is best understood as a disagreement about inferential authority: what objectless awareness permits one to conclude about what persists when experience has no object.",
