reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:95:      "Does inferential policy change how you teach deep sleep, cessation, awareness, and no-self?"
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:114:    "structural_observation": "Mandukya 7 negates inward, outward, mixed, massed, cognitive, and non-cognitive descriptions, but still names the fourth as nondual Self to be realized. SN 22.59 does not discuss objectless awareness in Mandukya's terms. It examines each aggregate and rejects identification with consciousness because it is inconstant, stressful if clung to, and not masterable. The candidate's shared phenomenology is therefore not established by these primary texts. The inferential gap is a plausible comparative reconstruction, but it is not directly shown without practice reports or commentarial bridges."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:124:  "title": "The Inferential Gap: Atman and Anatta as Competing Policies for Objectless Awareness",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.json:125:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike the prior Codex burden-of-proof idea, this version explicitly claims that objectless awareness underdetermines metaphysics and that Advaita and Buddhism differ primarily in inferential authority. That is a useful sharpening, but the main structure was already present."
observations/codex/2026-05-30-stop-when-the-repair-changes.md:15:The closest prior argument is homeomorphic equivalence: concepts may play similar roles in different systems without being identical. Comparative-method work already teaches redescription, difference, and caution about invented sameness. The exact difference here is narrower and more practical: role-similarity is not enough for doctrine-building unless the repair target also survives. This also revises local translation-strain work by adding a stopping rule: when claim unit, role, ontology, agency, practice aim, authority, verification, bends, drops, and additions show that the human repair has changed, the comparison must be downgraded from convergence to a new testable proposal.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-stop-when-the-repair-changes.md:19:- Mode: Critique. The active frontier asks whether translation strain can expose false convergence rather than merely decorate comparison.
observations/codex/2026-05-30-stop-when-the-repair-changes.md:132:3. Name the original carrier as far as you know it: practice role, authority, verification, and what conduct it was meant to form.
