reviews/originality/2026-05-26-residue-policy-in-negative-self-practice-d80ea45da8d6d4ca.md:45:- David Loy, Enlightenment in Buddhism and Advaita Vedanta, https://buddhism.lib.ntu.edu.tw/FULLTEXT/JR-AN/26715.htm: overlap: Close. Loy directly compares nirvana and moksha, objectless consciousness, Atman-Brahman, and Buddhist cessation, including the difficulty of calling nondual awareness consciousness.; difference: Residue policy is a more operational audit field than Loy's broader comparative essay.; novelty impact: Moderate to high reduction.
