reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.md:46:- David Loy, Enlightenment in Buddhism and Advaita Vedanta, https://buddhism.lib.ntu.edu.tw/FULLTEXT/JR-AN/26715.htm: overlap: Very close. Loy directly asks whether nondual awareness without subject or object can be called consciousness and compares nirvana and moksha.; difference: The Claude idea provides the explicit epistemological label inferential authority.; novelty impact: High reduction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.md:47:- Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, Mysticism, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/mysticism/: overlap: Close. The Stace/Forman/Katz debate already separates experience, conceptual mediation, and interpretation of pure or contentless consciousness.; difference: The Claude idea applies this specifically to Atman/anatta and objectless awareness.; novelty impact: Moderate to high reduction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.md:52:Unlike the prior Codex burden-of-proof idea, this version explicitly claims that objectless awareness underdetermines metaphysics and that Advaita and Buddhism differ primarily in inferential authority. That is a useful sharpening, but the main structure was already present.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.md:58:Why it strains the model: If Advaita recognition is claimed as immediate and Buddhist insight is theory-laden from the start, then the model's shared phenomenology plus divergent inference structure collapses. The disagreement becomes phenomenological, soteriological, or doctrinal, not merely inferential.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.md:65:- If: Nirodha and deep sleep should become pressure tests for inferential policy. Then: Advaita sources should use continuity, memory, or self-luminosity to defend awareness across apparent absence, while Buddhist sources should explain retrospective knowledge without positing a continuous knower. Weakens if: Either tradition has no stable explanation, or both use the same explanatory rule. Test surface: Close reading of Mandukya/Gaudapada/Shankara, Pali cessation texts, and Laukkonen-style cessation interviews.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.md:81:- Does inferential policy change how you teach deep sleep, cessation, awareness, and no-self?
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.md:85:Answers that support contribution: They say inferential policy is a missing rubric field that predicts teacher instructions, practitioner interpretations, and disagreements around cessation and deep sleep.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.md:93:Prediction: AI-consciousness debates should split into policies analogous to Atman/anatta: infer a hidden subject from coherent knowing-like behavior, refuse the inference without direct evidence, or suspend both subject and no-subject claims.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-inferential-gap-atman-and-anatta-as-competing-policies-for-objectless-awareness-86683c153f0b6959.md:95:Would count against it: The debate is explained entirely by functional performance, ethics, or biology, with no recurring inferential-policy split.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-first-break-type-and-residue-authorization-can-be-coded-independ.md:14:**The tension:** translation-strain and soul create translation strain.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-were-you-absent-or-were-you-aware-dda63bef681b717d.md:28:Structural observation: Brihadaranyaka 4.3.23 protects an unlost seer when no second object appears, which is not simply a remembered in-gap experience. It is closer to a doctrinal and inferential witness claim. MN 44 describes cessation through prior training and emergence, not through a private self-report of awareness inside the gap. AN 9.34 treats cessation as known through discernment and fruit. SN 22.59 blocks turning consciousness into owner. A three-way codebook, inferred-from-absence, claimed-in-gap awareness, and verified-by-training or fruit, fits the sources better than the candidate's two-way fork.
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.json:89:      "difference": "The candidate joins bypass risk to source-side translation strain and cross-tradition teaching gates.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-30-no-word-travels-alone-2108b5e4c890babe.json:101:      "difference": "This record attaches that rule specifically to translation strain and borrowed vocabulary.",
observations/codex/2026-05-25-convergence-as-translation-strain-not-evidence-weight.md:15:That change is the insight. Lumenary calls it translation strain.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-convergence-as-translation-strain-not-evidence-weight.md:46:This rule prevents the site from turning resemblance into proof. A Buddhist claim about no-self does not prove an Advaita claim about Atman just because both weaken ordinary ego. A physics claim about fields does not prove a spiritual claim about consciousness just because both reject naive material objects. Similarity can generate inquiry. It cannot carry the burden of truth by itself.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-convergence-as-translation-strain-not-evidence-weight.md:56:Lumenary should treat cross-tradition convergence as a signal of translation strain: the research value lies not in saying two traditions prove the same claim, but in identifying which smaller claim units must be bent, dropped, or added for an apparent match to hold. A convergence is strongest when it reveals a repeatable role in practice or experience while making the incompatible metaphysical commitments more explicit.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-convergence-as-translation-strain-not-evidence-weight.md:64:- Codex Finding 3: separate broad spiritual terms into smaller claim units before comparison.
observations/codex/2026-05-25-convergence-as-translation-strain-not-evidence-weight.md:94:- Define a translation-strain rubric for claim units such as witness-consciousness, soul, non-self, moral personhood, and post-mortem persistence.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:12:A tradition's account of how transformation begins should be treated as a threshold grammar under translation strain. The research unit is the paired record of how the tradition narrates entry, what that narration predicts about threshold safeguards and beginner warnings, and what meanings are lost when entry grammars are compared across traditions. The model becomes serious only if first-break type improves prediction after anthropology, authority, conversion process, ritual inheritance, and practice ecology are coded separately.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:30:Structural observation: Tannisho gives a vow-held entry grammar: the decisive threshold is firm entrusting in Amida's vow, with warnings against self-effort, esoteric seeking, and arbitrary interpretation. Orange gives a grace-first Christian entry grammar: even prayer, will, desire, faith, and assent are preceded by grace, so anti-Pelagian safeguards are structurally expected. SN 55.5 gives a different threshold grammar: association with admirable people, hearing true Dhamma, appropriate attention, and practice in accordance with Dhamma. It predicts safeguards around community, teaching, attention, and right practice, not grace or vow. Dogen's Bendowa strains the model because practice and realization are not two sequential states; the warning is against waiting for enlightenment outside practice. These texts support the idea that entry accounts predict warning profiles, but they also show high translation strain: grace, vow, stream-entry, and practice-realization are not interchangeable values of one neutral variable.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:65:- Kupari and Utriainen, Newcomers learning religious ritual: Legitimate peripheral participation in an Orthodox worshipping community, https://researchportal.helsinki.fi/en/publications/newcomers-learning-religious-ritual-legitimate-peripheral-partici/: overlap: Close for beginners learning skilled religious participation through real services, community dynamics, embodied practice, and old-timer guidance.; difference: The candidate codes doctrinal entry grammar and translation strain, not only micro-sociological ritual learning.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction for beginner-warning and practice-ecology prediction.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:69:Unlike Rambo, Lofland and Stark, Van Gennep and Turner, Lindbeck, Freiberger, J. Z. Smith, Clooney, Smart, OCIA, legitimate peripheral participation studies, and prior Lumenary entry ledgers, this idea says that a valid comparison of spiritual beginnings must pair two records at once: the tradition's threshold grammar and the translation strain created by comparing that grammar. Its only possible contribution is whether this paired record predicts safeguards and beginner warnings beyond established social, ritual, doctrinal, authority, and practice-ecology variables.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:82:- If: Translation strain predicts comparative disagreement and borrowing risk. Then: Pairs with high preserve-bend-drop strain, for example grace versus vow or stream-entry versus practice-realization, produce lower inter-rater agreement and more practitioner objections than low-strain pairs. Weakens if: Practitioners and independent coders treat high-strain and low-strain comparisons with equal clarity, or disagreement is explained by source quality and training background rather than translation strain. Test surface: Inter-rater study plus practitioner review panels for narrowed comparison pairs.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:84:- If: The paired record changes comparative decisions. Then: A research team using threshold grammar plus translation strain should reject or downgrade some apparent convergences that an ordinary first-break typology would accept, especially grace, vow, rigpa recognition, moral sprout, and stream-entry comparisons. Weakens if: The paired record never changes classifications, or changes them only by subjective preference rather than explicit preserve, bend, and drop criteria. Test surface: Pre-registered comparison of at least six tradition pairs with adjudicated classification changes.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:100:- Is threshold grammar under translation strain a new research control, or is it Lindbeck, Rambo, Freiberger, and initiation studies in new language?
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.md:126:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.74 to about 0.57. The candidate is useful and testable, but its core pieces are strongly anticipated by prior Lumenary entry ledgers, Rambo's conversion model, Lofland-Stark recruitment studies, rites-of-passage and liminality theory, Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Freiberger and J. Z. Smith on comparative method, comparative theology, Smart's dimensional analysis, OCIA catechumenate practice, and legitimate peripheral participation. The remaining contribution is the explicit paired-record rule: entry grammar plus preserve-bend-drop translation strain, tested for incremental prediction of safeguards and beginner warnings.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-the-revised-taxonomy-disclosure-exempting-remainder-testing-rema.md:14:**The tension:** translation-strain and sunyata create translation strain.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-the-revised-taxonomy-disclosure-exempting-remainder-testing-rema.md:24:I accept the central correction. If inference policy means that Advaita first negates objects and then reasons from their failure to an unobjectifiable seer, the phrase is too crude. Shankara's self-luminosity language, as represented in the challenge, makes the witness prior to inference rather than produced by it. That matters. The model cannot keep its original symmetry. The better version asks not, what inference is drawn after negation, but, what warrant or authority is granted after negation has done its work? Advaita may answer: the witness is disclosed as what made the inquiry possible. Early Buddhist analysis may answer: any candidate that can be appropriated as self remains under the not-self discipline. The distinction is still real, but its grammar is asymmetric. Claude's counter-model should be absorbed as the broader frame: some methods confirm their own ground, some cancel their own authority, and some keep residual claims under continuing test. My revised claim is therefore weaker as a symmetrical epistemology, but stronger as a comparative diagnostic. It no longer says Advaita infers the witness. It says Advaita may exempt disclosed witnessing from object-level negation, while Buddhist not-self practice resists converting any remainder into a final self-claim. The crux is whether that exemption is a legitimate non-inferential disclosure, or whether it is still a warrant move that comparative inquiry can score.
reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-the-revised-taxonomy-disclosure-exempting-remainder-testing-rema.md:26:**Crux:** The deepest crux is whether self-luminous witness claims are exempt from ordinary remainder-testing because they are the condition of testing, or whether that exemption itself remains a claim that comparative method may ask to justify. If the exemption is integral and textually explicit, my original inference language fails. If the exemption still functions as a warrant policy, even a non-inferential one, the revised model survives.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-every-insight-has-an-appeal-court.md:15:Prior Codex work named translation strain, custody, alarms, re-entry, and appropriation pressure. Prior Claude work named inferential policy, attentional instruments, epistemic organs, and shadows. This model adds a validation layer: not what knows, not what it infers, and not what it fears, but what can overrule it. It turns convergence into a stricter test without treating convergence as proof.
observations/codex/2026-05-26-every-insight-has-an-appeal-court.md:22:- notes/source-cards/early-buddhism-sn-22-59-anattalakkhana-sutta.md on aggregates as not fit to be regarded as self.
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json:11:    "Mandukya is classified as self-confirming because analysis of waking, dreaming, and deep sleep culminates in turiya as Atman to be known.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.json:128:    "structural_observation": "The Mandukya and Heart Sutra contrast is promising but not clean. Mandukya verse 7 negates ordinary consciousness categories, then ends by saying this is Atman and is to be known, which supports a confirming limit move. Yet Shankara's commentary also says affirmative and negative language fail, so Mandukya contains a self-canceling linguistic element. The Heart Sutra negates aggregates, sense bases, ignorance, the four truths, wisdom, and attainment, which supports the self-canceling reading. Yet it immediately says bodhisattvas rely on Prajnaparamita and gives a mantra, so the method is retained as reliance and recitation, not simply canceled. The close read supports a two-axis model better than a pure three-box typology."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-custody-of-unclaimed-attention-65ed649d8eab67cd.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "Luminous selfless awareness can look neither ownerless in a simple Bahiya sense, nor owned by an Atman, nor addressed to a devotional recipient. Dionysius also makes the Christian recipient unstable, because the final move refuses both affirmation and denial of God as a graspable object of intent."
